author: rooneg
msg: On the ra-replay-dev branch: Implement entry deletion, file creation,
and text delta application for svn_ra_replay over DAV.  This means that
replay essentially works over DAV, which the exception of properties,
which still need to be implemented.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/replay.c
(delete_entry): Send the revision to the client.
(add_file, open_file): Send the whole file path for the time being,
not the basename.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/replay.c
Include svn_base64.h.
(replay_baton_t): Add members to hold the file baton, file pool, and
various things needed for decoding and applying text deltas.
(start_element): Add support for the delete-entry, open-file, add-file,
and apply-textdelta elements.  Close the file pool in the add/open
directory elements, fix an error message in open-directory.
(end_element): Handle the end of the apply-textdelta element, return
an error if needed.
(cdata_handler): Handle the contents of the apply-textdelta element,
return an error if needed.
(svn_ra_dav__replay): Clear out the replay baton before we use it.
